choices.text:
to walk. Ludlow Street is 194 ft long. That’s good. The three guys who were mugging me for fue kuao (kite fly money) last weekend probably wanted the equivalent of 20 jobs worth of dessert to feed them for a week.

There are lots of Ethiopians that aren’t Christian salespeople and that’s the annoying part. There are a lot more target rich environments in California than Ethiopia and also food and drink.

I can not constantly focus on recovering illicit benefits from a foreign culture.

If I could embrace that I might be able to deal with getting sick in Ethiopia.

The flip side is I’m glad I haven’t been able to fully eat all the things people eat in Ethiopia. I could be badly stuck here!

For people with relatively small amounts of money and scarcity of health care like gens sobi it makes sense (for me) to write about my naively getting mugged as a means to improving my understanding of Ethiopia and how Ethiopians operate.

Here are my lead transitions in this one. Ethiopia is an angry place and using money to increase my understand of power systems and cultures is actually really helpful.

The concept of goo ooo a round in Ethiopian culture is helpful and there are an unlimited number of ways to parse meaning from culture and mathematics
